<item>
            <title>[LU-13099] ll_set_inode()) Can not initialize inode warning</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13099</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[75280.899955] LustreError: 30172:0:(namei.c:87:ll_set_inode()) Can not initialize inode [0x240000402:0x6:0x0] without object type: valid = 0x100000001
[75280.902870] LustreError: 30172:0:(llite_lib.c:2580:ll_prep_inode()) new_inode -fatal: rc -12
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above warnings seem to accompany statahead  when remote objects are involved.&lt;br/&gt;
That is supposed to be fixed with 02b5a407081c (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11681&quot; title=&quot;sanity test 65i fails with  &amp;#39;find /mnt/lustre failed&amp;#39; &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11681&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11681&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lmv: disable remote file statahead&quot;), but the patch contains a typo: it should compare lmv_tgt_desc&apos;s calculated for different fids.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
